&lt;p&gt;Review request for Flume and Arvind Prabhakar.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Summary&lt;br/&gt;
-------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sink runner&apos;s stop method first calls stop() to underlying sink and then shuts down the PollingRunner thread. If that thread is in middle of process, it leads to race conditions in the sink&apos;s process() and stop().&lt;br/&gt;
Rather than making all sinks to handle concurrently process() and stop(), its safer to shutdown the runner thread first and then stop the sink.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This addresses bug &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLUME-1110&quot; title=&quot;HDFS Sink throws IllegalStateException when flume-daemon shuts down&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLUME-1110&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLUME-1110&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLUME-1110&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLUME-1110&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


